  <sect1 xml:id="uptime-intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
      The system uptime tracking feature monitors when a client system is up. It
      works on an hourly basis&mdash;the system is considered up if it was
      running at any part of the given hour. The information is stored in &scc;
      (SCC) and Repository Mirroring Tool (RMT), and serves as a source for
      analytic purposes. The uptime tracking is disabled by default.
    </para>
  </sect1>
